<Rate>5< /Rate>< Review>
A long stay in the neighborhood, with the oldest brick oven in Los Angeles. The oven definitely brings out unique flavor.

Now I know why the locals keep coming back. When this COVID is over I want to try the dining room.

I tried a large pizza 1/2 pepperoni, 1/2 pastrami. And it was excellent! Brix is now my favorite pizzeria in South Los Angeles.

Thanks Brix for making my day! Keep up the good work üëç.< /Review>

The pizza, was mediocre at best. But I didn‚Äôt expect much considering the price. The taste of the pizza was not the issue. The customer service at this place is sub par to say the least.

Because I didn‚Äôt arrive within 10 mins of placing my order, the chicken wings I ordered were sold. The girl‚Äôs exact words were, ‚Äú You took too long so I sold them‚Äù. She also stated, ‚ÄúIf someone would have wanted your pizzas I would have sold those too‚Äù.

I placed this order on a Friday night. How do you run out of food on a Friday night, sale items ordered over the phone and then not offer an alternative???

Needless to say, this was my first and last time being a patron at Brix<//Review>

Pizza is ok, nothing to wow about like the other people who've reviewed this place but for the price it was good I payed $8 for a large pepperoni pizza with jalapeno and mushrooms which was a steal according to pricing these days and as for the pasta it was definitely a big flop I ordered fettuccine Alfredo with chicken...... Let start with the pasta it was spaghetti not fettuccine and the sauce was completely broken and watery and also grainy all at the same time the flavor wasn't bad but u can tell it definitely wasn't fresh or probably came out of a jar u buy at the store and the breadstick which was a single breadstick by the way was horrible.</Review>

< text>
10/16/2018 Our car was going into the shop after having been rear ended last week, our insurance company arranged a rental through this location. A lady called to set up the rental over the phone yesterday both my husband and I were on speaker phone with her and she told us the car wouldn't be ready until *after* 12:30 today.

We run a small business and were unable to get down there until shortly after 1pm. No car. They rented the car to someone else because we weren't there right at 12:30 on the dot. They claimed we had been told on the phone that we needed to be there right at 12:30 - both of us were on the phone and no such thing was said. And, it was an semi-extensive conversation as she took down all of our personal info (drivers license, etc.) supposedly to expedite the rental process and was sure to tell us we needed to pay a $50 deposit.

So in all that detail she didn't make clear or emphasize AT ALL that we needed to be there right at 12:30 - but she was sure certain to make sure we told her EXACTLY what car repair shop our personal car was going to be at - not sure why she needed to know but she waited while we dug through paperwork to get the information.

When explaining this to the person behind the desk at the office the only reply received was, "that's not how we do things." So much for customer service.

Our insurance company arranged the rental. Our car was going into the shop for 2+ days - it isn't like we weren't going to show up to get the car.

I've rented numerous cars and have never run into this sort of outrageous nonsense.

Customer service here is atrocious.

Updated 10/17/2018 to add:

Called my insurance agent who made some phone calls and magically, Enterprise on Rosedale managed to get me a car by 5pm - when previously I had only been offered a more expensive truck or nothing until the following day at 3pm.

I was treated to a pre-rental inspection of the car from stem to stern with all the courtesy and professionalism law enforcement typically reserves for the common criminal pulled over at the side of the highway.

To take the cake, this morning I find myself trapped in a GROUP TEXT MESSAGE sent to numerous other customers from the cell phone of some employee at this establishment - asking if there was anything we could do to improve their service. So, now my phone is going off every few minutes with people complaining about that (I was one of the people who complained).

When scraping the bottom of the barrel of customer service and setting the bar as absolutely low as possible - the professionalism, courtesy, and service of this establishment is absolutely unmatched.< /text>

<response>None</response><user_name>Monique Bittner<//user_name>< Review>
My experience at Shasta Orthopedic has not been very good. Way overpriced for what you receive. I have been put on hold multiple times for way too long. This afternoon I was put on hold for 30 minutes waiting for the billing department to answer. When I decided to call back because I figured they forgot me the office was then closed.

Shasta Orthopedic billing is very confusing and even the woman I spoke with admitted that it was confusing. She told me my bill was paid off and one day later I received another bill for $250. Watch for hidden costs like laying on a traction pillow while you wait for the chiropractor to see you and then be charged $45 extra for that service. Since many insurances pay for a basic adjustment, all the additional charges are out of pocket. Discuss with the doctors everything they do and ask them if you will be charged for it. I sure wish I had done that.< /Review>

Wow, I'm rambling but I did want people to know how good it felt to be treated with the respect and kindness everyone deserves. Cudos for Shasta Orthopaedics, Dr. Jenkinson and his staff. GOD BLESS AND THANK YOU ALL!.........Well, I was referred to Dr. Ferraro and he he did surgery on my hand and wrist. < review>
I am so glad that I used liberty plumbing who took care of myriad issues that I had with a new home.

2.  My furnace and air conditioning setups were not to code and in fact the mounting of the furnace was a complete disaster. < text>
Saturday morning we were awakened by a drip-drip-drip from the ceiling, which turned out to be a pinhole leak in a cold water line in our attic. The timing could not have been worse, as we were hosting a party that afternoon at 4!

Deanna was super responsive, and at 11 committed to have a tech do the work in time for the party. When I hadn't heard by 1:30, I checked in. Her tech had run into problems with the job he was currently working on. She and Justin (and the other client) teamed up to suspend the other job for a few hours to get our leak fixed.

Justin arrived at 2:40 and did a thorough and professional job. He had to crawl hands-and-knees through our hot attic, but he had it fixed and tested before our first guests arrived. He even offered the Angie's List discount unprompted!

Liberty Plumbing saved our party!< /text>

< Review>
Called Liberty concerning a suspected hot water slab leak in my kitchen & a team arrived ahead of schedule the next morning.  Both Kade & Sargon were professional, courteous & hard-working throughout the discovery, diagnosis & repair phases.  Kade was thoughtful & methodical is his approach & successfully determined the source of the leak, then provided me with several repair options & estimated costs.  They worked straight through the day & into the evening to complete the reroute through the attic using pex piping/new copper fittings, & water service was fully restored before they left.  I appreciated their neatness in wearing gloves & boot covers, laying down mats & tarps, & cleaning up at the end of the project.  Kade was both informative & knowledgeable, answering all my questions.  I was very pleased with the outcome & would highly recommend them for any plumbing needs. < Review>
I called Liberty plumbing on Monday morning because of a clogged drain leading from the kitchen sink to the main sewer line and Jerry said he would try to get someone out by afternoon.  This clogging has been a constant problem for the 20 years we have lived at this home and I was always able to clear it myself using a drain snake.  This time I could not get the drain clear.  Steve and his helper arrived at 11:30 Monday morning and using a combination of an electric powered snake and a gas powered water pressure hose they were able to clear the blockage.  I could not believe the junk that came out before they cleared the blockage.  It appeared to be white chunks of chalk or joint compound that may have been in that drain from the time of construction causing the many times I needed to snake out the line.

The service charge was exactly what was quoted.  I would highly recommend Liberty Plumbing.  .< /Review>

<username>Jess Lai< /username><time>1572946059636</time><rating>4< /rating>< review>
Store is small and cozy, with retro vibe. Not busy on a Monday night.
Food was good. BBQ sticks are average priced, at about $2/stick. Lamb scorpion pot was also good.
The potatoe was cut very thin and ended up floppy, the chicken skin was not crunchy at all but super soft and sweet, and the large shrimp was very small. I would not recommend these 3 items.
The wait time is horrible though. Despite the lack of customers, we still waited over 2 hours for our food. The server also forgot our orders for all the vegetables, and it wasn't until we had the manager check it that we found out. He ended up giving us a free beer and apple juice as apologize but it was still unacceptable since we ask the server to check but she kept brushing us off.
Would still recommend the food and restaurant but be ware.<//review>

<review>There are ups and downs to this place for sure. It's on the pricey side, but the location close to campus is amazing. The rooms are decently sized, and it's nice to have your own bathroom. The kitchen's are really nice, but one fridge is too little space for 4 people. The amenities are really nice, like the pool and fitness center (though a stair climber would be super nice to ad). It is frustrating though that they insist on packages being sent to the office despite the office taking a day or two to process them and sometimes forgetting to send emails about them being there (which they require for pickup). Management is really nice and they try and do a lot of fun things for residents, but communication is problematic. If they say that they can do something for you or that you can do something, GET IT IN WRITING and make sure they put a note on the account because someone else will tell you something different or say they don't have record. For example, when I was moving in I told them I wanted a parking garage in my building, they said okay you are on the list. Then I got an email saying I wasn't. Then I called again and they once again said okay you have it. I also emailed about 5 times saying that I wanted it. Then they emailed saying that no one signed up for the garage in our apartment so they gave it away to someone not living there, despite my numerous calls and emails saying I had it. If they say you are on a list or that you have gotten something GET PROOF and hold them to it.< /review><gmap_id>0x80c3518e345bb70d:0xc3701af7e52ad3a<//gmap_id>< Name>

I wish I was able to read the reviews before I thought about leasing but because it was "new" I was extremely excited. Boy how that changed quickly.
First, move in was delayed practically a month due to the apartments not ready to be moved into (when I leased and every time I called they PROMISED it would be finished in time)
I ended up living in a hotel for the first week of school at cal state.
Also, on my lease I indicated "quiet" and no late night party animals. What do I get? The complete opposite of that. The first few weeks there were loud parties to the point where I could not even study, living here really messed up with my school work due to not only the loud disrespectful roommates I had, but the parties going on around me with it.
So if you don't care about your school or studies, definitely come here.
During the school year there is no parking ever (due to the never ending parties) which forces you to park far away from the apartment you actually live in.
Not only ALL of this but the residents who live here are absolutely disrespectful. They leave the place a mess are obnoxiously loud and have no decency for others and security doesn't do anything. Honestly, if the people living here were better people I MIGHT have stayed, but we all know the population of the Glen ruins it for everyone.

The townhomes are very nice. The bedrooms are spacious and the pool area/clubhouse is also great. However, though the Glen staff is nice, they are disorganized and do not care to inform their residents. If you do get a spot, you have to pay for it and it may be a distance away from your townhome. We were not informed that this was going to happen and when we addressed it with the Glen staff, they said "someone should have told you about it." They recently charged a fee on everybody's account, but did not inform us or explain it until we called. There is little communication. <name>Joaquin Davalos< /name><Time>1604104117659<//Time>< rate>
1< /rate>
< Text>
The food was good but many other things were wrong. Health concerns.

It pains me to give a bad review but I hope it helps the business do better next time.
First of all I work in food service, I was out of work for a long time due to COVID-19 and it was hard finding a new job I lost a lot of income this year so my review has no political background.
I was excited to see this type of food and was eager to try it, I saw the tables outside with some deliciously looking plates so I had to try it.

My wife ordered and I went in to pick up the order, as I waited for the order I noticed how the person on the line plating the food was not wearing gloves, according to the California food code contact with ready to eat food (won't have any further preparation to be eaten) should be done with disposable gloves. Its the kind of stuff health inspectors fine during inspections.
The cashier who was handling cash from the tip jar jumped in to help plating the orders not wearing gloves, more importantly not washing his hands before touching the food. One of the cooks was opening some bags of condiments with his teeth.
None in the kitchen was wearing a face mask except the cashier.
I know the mask is uncomfortable in a hot kitchen by own experience, but its a reality we have to face for a few more months.
A close friend lost his father to COVID, a high-school classmate also died recently to the virus.

I didn't enjoy my food wondering if this was safe to eat or not.< /Text>

<rating>4</rating><Review>I discovered Meze at an event at the North Colombia School House before Meze opened down town. I was impressed with the quality and freshness of the food, as well as the authenticity and flavor of my  Falafel Plate. Service was friendly and prompt.
When Meze opened I was one of the first customers and enjoyed my beef and lamb gyro, with hot sauce. No complaints, although I thought the price tag of around $14 for a gyro seemed high, despite that the ingredients are claimed to be organic. I have tried and love the Vegan Bowl as well ( even though Im far from Vegan ).
The only complaint that I have is the tables are often dirty with food from the last person who sat there. I asked for the table to be cleaned once and the woman behind the counter begrudgingly came out and wiped the table, knocking food bits on to the floor, and my lap to my dismay. The table still had a layer of black grime that I had to wipe off with a paper napkin so that I could feel good about eating off the table. The bathroom trash is often over flowing, and there has been empty soap dispenser in the bathroom.

< UserId.>
115599545290522223554</UserId.>
<name>Vilina Hutter< /name><Date>1551983601987< /Date>< Rating>
4</Rating>
< Text>
Really new and different food for Grass Valley, MeZe offers Israeli/middle eastern food in a casual environment.   Typical menu items are in the range of $15 .  You can order pitas sandwiches or plates, which feature meat or falafel, for example,  with small servings of salads and dressings.   I've had both a sandwich and a falafel plate.  I enjoyed both, but the falafel was just a touch over crisp and dry.  Still good if dipped in sauce!
Food is ordered at the register, and your name is called when it's ready.  Someone needs to explain to me why a tip is suggested by the cash register software.  Since when do cashiers get tips?  Also, the cashier is responsible for the phone, which means divided attention.   Have someone else do the take out orders!
Seating is quite limited in this small eatery...less than 6 small tables and a counter.  Nowhere is comfort a consideration...the chairs are functional but do not encourage lingering!
The service can be kind of strange.  Pita sandwich halfs are served on a rack, oddly lodged into coffee filters.  That's just wierd, and not actually very effective for drippy hand held food like this.  Hopefully they will plow some of their profits into a better service solution!
Overall, this is  worthwhile place.  The prime mission of a restaurant is to serve good food, and MeZe does that.  It's fresh, made from scratch, unusual flavors, and plenty of vegetarian options.  The price is reasonable.  It's not  a comfy hang out dinner place, for sure, but for a quick tasty and healthy dinner, it is great.  And I bet the peripheral details will improve as they are in business longer.< /Text>

< review>
This is a really nice, clean store. I just moved to the area so I'm trying out every grocer within a half hour drive. There was a great selection of most things but my only hesitation is that there wasn't a huge selection of produce, acceptable but not amazing.  Maybe I'm mistaken but I think Vons are the same as Safeway and I know at Safeways the produce section can vary a lot by location.  The other thing I would like more selection of in an ideal world would be imports.  The international foods were very very limited. Everything they do carry was well stocked when I was there (Tuesday arvo) except a couple things people are still panic buying which is understandable. I appreciated too that there was a public toilet during covid times, a lot of places have them closed.</review>

<review>We visited this store simply because it was on our way home from another location, but we were very disappointed. The produce section was under stocked. At our local Albertsons, the bakery department gives free cookies to the kids. We went to the bakery department here to see if they do the same, and there was one worker busy helping somebody else. We waited about 10 minutes and finally gave up.
